article.description: Robert Morris 77, Mount St. Mary's, Md. 70
article.headline: Robert Morris 77, Mount St. Mary's, Md. 70
article.linkText: Robert Morris 77, Mount St. Mary's, Md. 70
article.story: EMMITSBURG, Md. -- Rob Robinson scored 17 points, grabbed nine rebounds and had three blocked shots to lead Robert Morris to a 77-70 win over Mount St. Mary's on Monday night. The Colonials (8-7, 3-1 Northeast Conference), used a 17-2 spurt early in the second half to rally from an 11-point first-half deficit. Robert Morris also outrebounded the Mountaineers 46-30 and had 18 second-chance points. Jeremy Chappell, who added 17 points and eight rebounds for the Colonials, had a three-point play with 1:55 left to seal the win. Robert Morris also was 10-for-12 from the free-throw line in the final 1:10. Jean Cajou scored 17 points for the Mountaineers (5-9, 0-3), who were hurt by their 10-for-19 performance from the foul line in the last nine minutes. Jeremy Goode, with 11 points, became the 40th player in Mount St. Mary's history to score 1,000 points.
